### 2026-04-07 — Design fix: upgrade-on default + settings UI + first-run notice

Dogfood feedback rejected the upgrade-off default that codex pass 1
P1 had endorsed. The flaw: opt-in via `config.toml` with no settings
UI is invisible — existing users would never discover the feature.
Same outcome as not shipping the feature at all.

Commit `506d8ab` reversed the design:
- `Config::load_with_migrations` no longer flips `shortcut_enabled`
  to `false`. It still detects the no-`[palette]`-section case and
  persists the default section, but the persisted value is `true`.
- New Tauri commands `cmd_palette_settings` + `cmd_set_palette_shortcut`
  mirroring `cmd_set_live_shortcut`.
- New COMMAND PALETTE row in the existing Settings overlay.
- One-shot first-run notification (`maybe_show_palette_first_run_notice`)
  fired from `setup()` after the shortcut registers, with a marker
  file at `~/.minutes/palette_first_run_shown` to prevent re-firing.

The codex pass 1 P1 framing was right about the harm scenario
(don't hijack VS Code's Delete Line silently) but wrong about the
mitigation. The right mitigation is "default on with discoverable
disable", not "default off with invisible enable."

